contents.desc: Senator John Kennedy interrogates the NCAA head about the fairness of allowing transgender women, who are biologically male, to compete against biological females in collegiate sports. Kennedy insists on the inherent physiological advantages of biological males, which the NCAA head initially calls "debatable" but then concedes under Kennedy's questioning. The discussion turns to legal precedents, with the NCAA head citing court decisions, while Kennedy pushes for the NCAA to show leadership by providing clarity on this contentious issue. #JohnKennedy #NCAA #TransgenderAthletes #SportsFairness
